# 01-CORE - Core Rules Directory

## Core Rules Directory

This directory contains fundamental rules and standards that apply to all parts of the Agent Player project.

## Files Structure

### 1. project-standards.mdc
- General project standards
- Core development standards
- Language and formatting rules

### 2. development-workflow.mdc
- Development workflow
- Git workflow
- Code review process

### 3. error-handling.mdc
- Error handling standards
- Exception handling
- Error recovery

### 4. logging-standards.mdc
- Logging standards
- Log levels
- Structured logging

### 5. code-quality.mdc
- Code quality standards
- Best practices
- Code standards

## Purpose

Define core standards that must be followed across all Agent Player project components to ensure:
- Development consistency
- High code quality
- Easy maintenance
- Optimized performance

## Usage

These rules apply to:
- Backend development
- Frontend development  
- Database design
- API development
- Testing
- Deployment
- Documentation

## MANDATORY Core Standards
- English only in all code and comments
- Consistent naming conventions across all files
- Proper error handling in all components
- Structured logging for all operations
- Code quality checks before commits
- Documentation for all major features
- Testing requirements for all functionality
- Security considerations in all implementations

